# JabRef REST API

// This file is for IntelliJ's HTTP Client, available in the Ultimate Edition

// Start the HTTP server using Gradle > JabRef > jabsrv-cli > Tasks > application > run

### Get a HTML page asking the user to go to /libraries

GET http://localhost:23119

### Get the list of all libraries

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries
Accept: application/json

### Query entries across all open libraries (single query)

// Each query is a Search.g4 expression. The DOI below is present in the bundled demo (Chocolate.bib),
// so this returns a match when the server is started without a library file.

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries:query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "queries": ["doi = \"10.1161/circulationaha.108.827022\""]
}

### Query entries across all open libraries (multiple queries, results returned in input order)

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries:query
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "queries": ["doi = \"10.1161/circulationaha.108.827022\"", "title = \"chocolate\""]
}

## demo cases

// JabRef ships with "Chocolate.bib", which is "magically" served when asking for "demo"

### Get JSON of Chocolate.bib

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo
Accept: application/json

### Get plain BibTeX of Chocolate.bib

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo
Accept: application/x-bibtex

### Get list of files in Chocolate.bib

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo/entries/pdffiles
Accept: application/json

### Get CSL JSON of Chocolate.bib

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo
Accept: application/x-bibtex-library-csl+json

### Read demo JabMap (Chocolate.jmp)

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo/map
Accept: application/json

### Save demo JabMap (Chocolate.jmp) note: this might break the data for the demo map

PUT http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo/map
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "demo"
}

### Get HTML-representation of entry preview for "Tokede_2011" of Chocolate.bib

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo/entries/Tokede_2011
Accept: text/html

### Get String-representation of entry preview for "Corti_2009" of Chocolate.bib

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo/entries/Corti_2009
Accept: text/plain

### Get BibTeX of Chocolate.bib

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo
Accept: application/x-bibtex

### Get JSON of Chocolate.bib

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo
Accept: application/json

### Get CSL JSON of Chocolate.bib

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/demo
Accept: application/x-bibtex-library-csl+json

## Error cases

### GET not available library

GET http://localhost:23119/libraries/notfound

## Creation

JabRef offers `current` for the currently selected tab

### Add BibTeX to current library

// Works in UI mode only

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/current/entries
Content-Type: application/x-bibtex

@article{demo,
  title = {Added by REST}
}

### Import RIS to current library

// Works in UI mode only

POST http://localhost:23119/libraries/current/entries
Content-Type: application/x-research-info-systems

TY  - CHAP
PY  - 2015
Y1  - 2015/09/10
Y2  - 2015/11/06
M1  - 0
DO  - doi:10.1201/b19107-2
UR  - http://dx.doi.org/10.1201/b19107-2
N1  - doi:10.1201/b19107-2
AU  - Catarina Barata
AU  - MEmre Celebi
AU  - JorgeS Marques
SP  - 1-22
TI  - Toward a Robust Analysis of Dermoscopy Images Acquired under Different Conditions
T2  - Dermoscopy Image Analysis
T3  - Digital Imaging and Computer Vision
SN  - 978-1-4822-5326-9
PB  - CRC Press
ER  -
